This paper is about improving language modeling for code completion, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper uses language models such as LSTM and attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel statement-level language model, which involves deep learning techniques such as BiLSTM and embedding generation, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper is focused on improving code completion, which is a task related to programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
